# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ShipLog environment. Copy to .env.local (git-ignored).
# Never commit real credentials.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# ShipLog talks to an Amazon Aurora DSQL *multi-region* cluster: two
# peered, active-active endpoints (Virginia + Singapore). Writes to either
# endpoint are strongly consistent across both. Auth is IAM — there is NO
# password; the "password" is a short-lived (~15 min) IAM auth token the
# DsqlSigner mints per physical connection.
#
# If NO DSQL host is set, ShipLog runs in MOCK mode (in-memory store) so the
# UI and the conflict/retry demo are explorable before you provision DSQL.
# Mock mode is labelled in the UI — it never pretends to be multi-region.

# ── Aurora DSQL endpoints (one per region of the multi-region cluster) ──
# Get these from the DSQL console after creating a multi-region cluster.
# DSQL_HOST_VIRGINIA=abc123def.dsql.us-east-1.on.aws
# DSQL_HOST_SINGAPORE=xyz789ghi.dsql.ap-southeast-1.on.aws

# Used by the db:schema / db:seed scripts (defaults to the Virginia host).
# DSQL_HOST=abc123def.dsql.us-east-1.on.aws
# DSQL_REGION=us-east-1

# ── IAM auth ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# PREFERRED (credential-less, hackathon-rewarded): Vercel OIDC federation.
# When AWS_ROLE_ARN is set, the DsqlSigner assumes it via Vercel OIDC — no keys.
# Locally this needs VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN, pulled by `vercel env pull .env.local`.
# AWS_ROLE_ARN=arn:aws:iam::000000000000:role/shiplog-dsql

# FALLBACK: static credentials with dsql:DbConnectAdmin permission (local only).
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# AWS_SESSION_TOKEN=
